Definition: an inclination to support or be loyal to or to agree with an opinion
Example: his sympathies were always with the underdog; I knew I could count on his understanding
Synonyms: adj, all, sympathetic, verb, cognition, sympathize, sympathise, understanding, understand, inclination, an, to, support, or, be, loyal, agree, with, opinion, his, sympathies, were, always, the, underdog, I, knew, could, count, on
Category: noun.cognition
